Text.SourceString: I was telling the mayor I didn’t think anyone would want to visit the island until we got rid of the oil on the beach, but you proved me wrong.//Welcome to the community!
Text.LocalizedString: I was telling the mayor I didn’t think anyone would want to visit the island until we got rid of the oil on the beach, but you proved me wrong.//Welcome to the community!

Text.SourceString: Yeah, you’re right. The island isn’t like it used to be.//It is what it is.
Text.LocalizedString: Yeah, you’re right. The island isn’t like it used to be.//It is what it is.

Text.SourceString: I like to spend my Spring mornings in Garden Lane.//<portrait=happy>It’s close by, and have you seen it? Incredibly gorgeous.
Text.LocalizedString: I like to spend my Spring mornings in Garden Lane.//<portrait=happy>It’s close by, and have you seen it? Incredibly gorgeous.

Text.SourceString: The museum is nice and warm now.//Not too hot, not too cold. It’s a comfortable place to work in Spring.
Text.LocalizedString: The museum is nice and warm now.//Not too hot, not too cold. It’s a comfortable place to work in Spring.

Text.SourceString: My brooch? Oh…//<portrait=normal>It’s special to me. Not expensive. Nothing like that.//<NPCName>Sunny</> gave it to me the day we brought <NPCName>Oliver</> home from Pokyo.
Text.LocalizedString: My brooch? Oh…//<portrait=normal>It’s special to me. Not expensive. Nothing like that.//<NPCName>Sunny</> gave it to me the day we brought <NPCName>Oliver</> home from Pokyo.

Text.SourceString: The heat can get intense at the beach this time of year.//<portrait=concerned>Even with the windows open, sometimes it’s still hot, even at night.
Text.LocalizedString: The heat can get intense at the beach this time of year.//<portrait=concerned>Even with the windows open, sometimes it’s still hot, even at night.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Suki</> has great bug repellent. I believe she makes it herself.//It comes in handy in Summer.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Suki</> has great bug repellent. I believe she makes it herself.//It comes in handy in Summer.

Text.SourceString: Oof! No more humidity. I have to use curlers on my hair now.//<portrait=normal>Good thing I have short hair.
Text.LocalizedString: Oof! No more humidity. I have to use curlers on my hair now.//<portrait=normal>Good thing I have short hair.

Text.SourceString: Oof! No more humidity. I have to use curlers on my hair now.//<portrait=normal>Good thing I have short hair.
Text.LocalizedString: Oof! No more humidity. I have to use curlers on my hair now.//<portrait=normal>Good thing I have short hair.

Text.SourceString: The Beach Shack has been smoking a lot of salmon lately.//<portrait=annoyed>The smoke gets trapped on the second floor all day… No matter how many times we change our clothes, we end up smelling like smoked salmon.
Text.LocalizedString: The Beach Shack has been smoking a lot of salmon lately.//<portrait=annoyed>The smoke gets trapped on the second floor all day… No matter how many times we change our clothes, we end up smelling like smoked salmon.

Text.SourceString: I’ve been telling those two that’s what happens, but nope. They still insist. All right, then. What can I say?//<NPCName>Jim</> and <NPCName>Sunny</> are in charge of the kitchen.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been telling those two that’s what happens, but nope. They still insist. All right, then. What can I say?//<NPCName>Jim</> and <NPCName>Sunny</> are in charge of the kitchen.

Text.SourceString: When a caterpillar spins its chrysalis, it’s an ugly little thing! But then a beautiful butterfly emerges.//And lychees are the same… Ugly on the outside, but soft and sweet on the inside.
Text.LocalizedString: When a caterpillar spins its chrysalis, it’s an ugly little thing! But then a beautiful butterfly emerges.//And lychees are the same… Ugly on the outside, but soft and sweet on the inside.

Text.SourceString: Well… I don’t know if that’s a very good analogy, to be honest.//I just know I love those little fruits!
Text.LocalizedString: Well… I don’t know if that’s a very good analogy, to be honest.//I just know I love those little fruits!

Text.SourceString: I’m glad we have a good coffee bar here in Starlet Town, but to tell you the truth, I much prefer green tea.//<portrait=happy>Don’t tell <NPCName>Raj</>!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m glad we have a good coffee bar here in Starlet Town, but to tell you the truth, I much prefer green tea.//<portrait=happy>Don’t tell <NPCName>Raj</>!

Text.SourceString: Green tea has a lot of health benefits. It may even protect the brain from aging! But mainly, I like the taste.
Text.LocalizedString: Green tea has a lot of health benefits. It may even protect the brain from aging! But mainly, I like the taste.

Text.SourceString: We’re always looking for donations at the museum. Please stop by if you have any interesting bugs you’d like to share!
Text.LocalizedString: We’re always looking for donations at the museum. Please stop by if you have any interesting bugs you’d like to share!

Text.SourceString: Catch any good bugs lately? Bring them to the museum if you want to contribute to our insect exhibit.
Text.LocalizedString: Catch any good bugs lately? Bring them to the museum if you want to contribute to our insect exhibit.

Text.SourceString: Oh gosh… It’s raining, all right.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh gosh… It’s raining, all right.

Text.SourceString: Oh gosh… It’s a storm, all right.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh gosh… It’s a storm, all right.

Text.SourceString: This rain isn’t good for our caterpillars! I covered the terrarium with a plastic bin. We don’t want those little guys to drown!//I’m going to go and cover the others.
Text.LocalizedString: This rain isn’t good for our caterpillars! I covered the terrarium with a plastic bin. We don’t want those little guys to drown!//I’m going to go and cover the others.

Text.SourceString: It’s raining pretty hard. I should be going home.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s raining pretty hard. I should be going home.

Text.SourceString: It’s raining pretty hard. I should be going home.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s raining pretty hard. I should be going home.

Text.SourceString: This rain isn’t good for our caterpillars! I covered the terrarium with a plastic bin. We don’t want those little guys to drown!//I’m going to go and cover the others.
Text.LocalizedString: This rain isn’t good for our caterpillars! I covered the terrarium with a plastic bin. We don’t want those little guys to drown!//I’m going to go and cover the others.

Text.SourceString: The museum is cold in Winter.//I guess the high ceiling doesn’t help. It gets <Italic>really</> cold sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: The museum is cold in Winter.//I guess the high ceiling doesn’t help. It gets <Italic>really</> cold sometimes.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes at night, I take <NPCName>Oliver</> to the porch on the second floor, and we watch the snow falling on the water.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes at night, I take <NPCName>Oliver</> to the porch on the second floor, and we watch the snow falling on the water.

Text.SourceString: I love watching butterflies move from flower to flower. They’re so graceful and elegant.
Text.LocalizedString: I love watching butterflies move from flower to flower. They’re so graceful and elegant.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Oliver’s</> given me an opportunity I didn’t think I’d ever have—being a mom.//If it weren’t for the bravery of his biological mother, my story would’ve been so different.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Oliver’s</> given me an opportunity I didn’t think I’d ever have—being a mom.//If it weren’t for the bravery of his biological mother, my story would’ve been so different.

Text.SourceString: Days like these make you think, don’t they?//It takes me back to when we first brought <NPCName>Oliver</> home.
Text.LocalizedString: Days like these make you think, don’t they?//It takes me back to when we first brought <NPCName>Oliver</> home.

Text.SourceString: I didn’t bond with him right away. I was worried, of course.//Maybe I wasn’t cut out to be – to be his mom. You know, those thoughts.//<portrait=annoyed>I didn’t fall in love right away, and back then I had so much shame.//<portrait=normal>All in the past now. Couldn’t imagine life without my son.
Text.LocalizedString: I didn’t bond with him right away. I was worried, of course.//Maybe I wasn’t cut out to be – to be his mom. You know, those thoughts.//<portrait=annoyed>I didn’t fall in love right away, and back then I had so much shame.//<portrait=normal>All in the past now. Couldn’t imagine life without my son.

Text.SourceString: Days like these make you think, don’t they?//It takes me back to when we first brought <NPCName>Oliver</> home.
Text.LocalizedString: Days like these make you think, don’t they?//It takes me back to when we first brought <NPCName>Oliver</> home.

Text.SourceString: I didn’t bond with him right away. I was worried, of course.//Maybe I wasn’t cut out to be – to be his mom. You know, those thoughts.//<portrait=annoyed>I didn’t fall in love right away, and back then I had so much shame.//<portrait=normal>All in the past now. Couldn’t imagine life without my son.
Text.LocalizedString: I didn’t bond with him right away. I was worried, of course.//Maybe I wasn’t cut out to be – to be his mom. You know, those thoughts.//<portrait=annoyed>I didn’t fall in love right away, and back then I had so much shame.//<portrait=normal>All in the past now. Couldn’t imagine life without my son.

Text.SourceString: At first, right after we brought <NPCName>Oliver</> home, I thought I wasn’t mom material.//Doubts… They get to you sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: At first, right after we brought <NPCName>Oliver</> home, I thought I wasn’t mom material.//Doubts… They get to you sometimes.

Text.SourceString: But eventually, it just felt like everything fell into place.//<portrait=normal>I don’t know how or when it started. The next thing I knew, he called me Mom.//And that’s who I’ve been ever since.
Text.LocalizedString: But eventually, it just felt like everything fell into place.//<portrait=normal>I don’t know how or when it started. The next thing I knew, he called me Mom.//And that’s who I’ve been ever since.

Text.SourceString: I always knew deep down that being a mom was something I was meant to do, and adopting <NPCName>Oliver</> just confirmed it.//Even when it didn’t go as well as I thought it would at first.
Text.LocalizedString: I always knew deep down that being a mom was something I was meant to do, and adopting <NPCName>Oliver</> just confirmed it.//Even when it didn’t go as well as I thought it would at first.

Text.SourceString: I’d been waiting to be a mom for so long.//<portrait=concerned>And <NPCName>Sunny</> – of course, he was meant to be a dad. You can just tell these things.//I knew it the moment he met my nieces.
Text.LocalizedString: I’d been waiting to be a mom for so long.//<portrait=concerned>And <NPCName>Sunny</> – of course, he was meant to be a dad. You can just tell these things.//I knew it the moment he met my nieces.

Text.SourceString: Some kids came to the museum the other day, and oh gosh… <NPCName>Scott</> sure loves kids, and kids adore him!//<portrait=normal>He reminds me a lot of <NPCName>Sunny</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Some kids came to the museum the other day, and oh gosh… <NPCName>Scott</> sure loves kids, and kids adore him!//<portrait=normal>He reminds me a lot of <NPCName>Sunny</>.

Text.SourceString: It’s interesting how flies can sense when something is rotting or decaying. It’s like they have a sixth sense or something.//Morbid, I know.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s interesting how flies can sense when something is rotting or decaying. It’s like they have a sixth sense or something.//Morbid, I know.

Text.SourceString: I feel bad for flies. Everybody seems to hate them, but they’re just trying to do their part in the world.
Text.LocalizedString: I feel bad for flies. Everybody seems to hate them, but they’re just trying to do their part in the world.

Text.SourceString: I mean, sure, flies can be a nuisance when they’re around your food, but they’re just looking for a meal like any other living thing.
Text.LocalizedString: I mean, sure, flies can be a nuisance when they’re around your food, but they’re just looking for a meal like any other living thing.

Text.SourceString: You might think there are more flies in Summer than any other time of year, but that’s actually not true.//<portrait=normal>Yeah, maybe in some parts of the world, but here in Starlet Town, the flies are out year-round.
Text.LocalizedString: You might think there are more flies in Summer than any other time of year, but that’s actually not true.//<portrait=normal>Yeah, maybe in some parts of the world, but here in Starlet Town, the flies are out year-round.

Text.SourceString: Summertime here is lively!//<portrait=happy>The beach, the shack. People are vivacious.
Text.LocalizedString: Summertime here is lively!//<portrait=happy>The beach, the shack. People are vivacious.

Text.SourceString: I can’t believe it’s already Summer. Time flies, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t believe it’s already Summer. Time flies, huh?

Text.SourceString: I’m thinking of replanting my garden outside the bedroom.//Do you have any good gardening tips?
Text.LocalizedString: I’m thinking of replanting my garden outside the bedroom.//Do you have any good gardening tips?

Text.SourceString: If I plant flowers this Spring, what do you think I should grow? Peonies or daisies?
Text.LocalizedString: If I plant flowers this Spring, what do you think I should grow? Peonies or daisies?

Text.SourceString: The salty air in front of the shack makes it hard for plants to grow. A lot of them end up dying, and the bushes are all that’s left.
Text.LocalizedString: The salty air in front of the shack makes it hard for plants to grow. A lot of them end up dying, and the bushes are all that’s left.

Text.SourceString: The only thing I need in this sleepy weather is a cup of green tea.
Text.LocalizedString: The only thing I need in this sleepy weather is a cup of green tea.

Text.SourceString: I can’t believe it’s already Fall. Where did Summer go?
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t believe it’s already Fall. Where did Summer go?

Text.SourceString: I’m surprised a lot, aren’t I?//Well, what can I say? The change of seasons always takes me by surprise. A good kind of surprise!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m surprised a lot, aren’t I?//Well, what can I say? The change of seasons always takes me by surprise. A good kind of surprise!

Text.SourceString: I’m thinking of having a bonfire tomorrow evening with <NPCName>Oliver</> and maybe some of his friends.//It would be in front of the inn, not by the shack. There’s just more room for the kids to play.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m thinking of having a bonfire tomorrow evening with <NPCName>Oliver</> and maybe some of his friends.//It would be in front of the inn, not by the shack. There’s just more room for the kids to play.

Text.SourceString: We may not do it, though. <NPCName>Oliver</> doesn’t like going out at night.
Text.LocalizedString: We may not do it, though. <NPCName>Oliver</> doesn’t like going out at night.

Text.SourceString: I can’t wait for the Winter Fair.//The beach is lively again. The best part is we can see the pretty lights from the shack.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t wait for the Winter Fair.//The beach is lively again. The best part is we can see the pretty lights from the shack.

Text.SourceString: We’ve been making ramen at the shack lately.//<portrait=normal>Maybe I’ll roast some chestnuts tonight. It’s <NPCName>Sunny’s</> favorite.//<portrait=happy>We still have some chestnuts from Fall… I hope.
Text.LocalizedString: We’ve been making ramen at the shack lately.//<portrait=normal>Maybe I’ll roast some chestnuts tonight. It’s <NPCName>Sunny’s</> favorite.//<portrait=happy>We still have some chestnuts from Fall… I hope.

Text.SourceString: It’s nice to see kids enjoying the snow and building snowmen.//<portrait=normal>Some of the kids I used to watch building snowmen a long time ago are grown up now. The twins who run the inn, <NpcName>Frankie Jr.</> … //<portrait=happy>Gosh! I’m old!
Text.LocalizedString: It’s nice to see kids enjoying the snow and building snowmen.//<portrait=normal>Some of the kids I used to watch building snowmen a long time ago are grown up now. The twins who run the inn, <NpcName>Frankie Jr.</> … //<portrait=happy>Gosh! I’m old!

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Sunny</> can be loud sometimes. But that’s just his personality.//<portrait=normal>Yeah, and his voice.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Sunny</> can be loud sometimes. But that’s just his personality.//<portrait=normal>Yeah, and his voice.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Sunny</> and I went to the parent-teacher meeting last week. We got to talking to the other parents.//<portrait=surprised>I was looking at <NpcName>Paul</> and <NpcName>Anne</>. My gosh, they’re young!//<portrait=concerned>I wonder if we started this parenting thing too late.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Sunny</> and I went to the parent-teacher meeting last week. We got to talking to the other parents.//<portrait=surprised>I was looking at <NpcName>Paul</> and <NpcName>Anne</>. My gosh, they’re young!//<portrait=concerned>I wonder if we started this parenting thing too late.

Text.SourceString: If we had more room, I’d love to have an insect house or two. I’d get one now, but where would we put it?//<portrait=surprised>It would take up the whole kitchen.
Text.LocalizedString: If we had more room, I’d love to have an insect house or two. I’d get one now, but where would we put it?//<portrait=surprised>It would take up the whole kitchen.

Text.SourceString: The fish pond could be very useful. You could put fish in it, and they multiply.
Text.LocalizedString: The fish pond could be very useful. You could put fish in it, and they multiply.

Text.SourceString: There’s a very informative TV show called The Bug’s Life.//<portrait=surprised>Oh no, no! That’s a different show.//<portrait=normal>It’s Back to Nature. The host gives information about when certain bugs come out and things like that.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s a very informative TV show called The Bug’s Life.//<portrait=surprised>Oh no, no! That’s a different show.//<portrait=normal>It’s Back to Nature. The host gives information about when certain bugs come out and things like that.

Text.SourceString: The host is <NpcName>Luke’s</> cousin, Jenna. I overheard him telling <NpcName>Sunny</> about it.//<portrait=normal>I thought it was neat.
Text.LocalizedString: The host is <NpcName>Luke’s</> cousin, Jenna. I overheard him telling <NpcName>Sunny</> about it.//<portrait=normal>I thought it was neat.

Text.SourceString: I was going over <NpcName>Oliver’s</> homework yesterday, and I understood <Italic>nothing</>. The math they teach these days is beyond complicated.//<portrait=surprised>I don’t remember it having so many letters.
Text.LocalizedString: I was going over <NpcName>Oliver’s</> homework yesterday, and I understood <Italic>nothing</>. The math they teach these days is beyond complicated.//<portrait=surprised>I don’t remember it having so many letters.

Text.SourceString: You can find all kinds of things in the ocean.//<portrait=surprised>This one time, <NpcName>Jim’s</> boy brought us a treasure chest. I said, “What are we supposed to do with this?”
Text.LocalizedString: You can find all kinds of things in the ocean.//<portrait=surprised>This one time, <NpcName>Jim’s</> boy brought us a treasure chest. I said, “What are we supposed to do with this?”

Text.SourceString: We didn’t have the tools to open a treasure chest, so I told <NpcName>Theo</> to take it to the blacksmith and to keep whatever was in it.
Text.LocalizedString: We didn’t have the tools to open a treasure chest, so I told <NpcName>Theo</> to take it to the blacksmith and to keep whatever was in it.

Text.SourceString: I’ve prepared myself for when <NpcName>Oliver</> asks about his biological mother.//<portrait=normal>I’d like to think that when the time comes, I’m ready to answer questions and support his decisions, whatever they might be.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve prepared myself for when <NpcName>Oliver</> asks about his biological mother.//<portrait=normal>I’d like to think that when the time comes, I’m ready to answer questions and support his decisions, whatever they might be.

Text.SourceString: I rarely buy clothes at White Flamingo.//<portrait=annoyed>Everything costs way too much there.
Text.LocalizedString: I rarely buy clothes at White Flamingo.//<portrait=annoyed>Everything costs way too much there.

Text.SourceString: Blue morpho butterflies are really rare, but they do exist here.//I’ve seen them flying around the lake in Summer.
Text.LocalizedString: Blue morpho butterflies are really rare, but they do exist here.//I’ve seen them flying around the lake in Summer.

Text.SourceString: Oh, by the way. I’ve been meaning to tell you this. You do so much for this community, <PlayerName>$Player</>.//<portrait=happy>I’m so grateful for you. The environment around us is better now because of you.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, by the way. I’ve been meaning to tell you this. You do so much for this community, <PlayerName>$Player</>.//<portrait=happy>I’m so grateful for you. The environment around us is better now because of you.

Text.SourceString: Crickets are in full force now that the ice has melted.//They’ll be out till the end of Summer. Watch out!
Text.LocalizedString: Crickets are in full force now that the ice has melted.//They’ll be out till the end of Summer. Watch out!

Text.SourceString: I miss the sound of crickets.//There isn’t any more cricket song when we open our windows, but that’s all right. They’ll be back soon enough.
Text.LocalizedString: I miss the sound of crickets.//There isn’t any more cricket song when we open our windows, but that’s all right. They’ll be back soon enough.

Text.SourceString: It’s starting to get chilly out.//I’ll need a warmer jacket soon. This one won’t do.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s starting to get chilly out.//I’ll need a warmer jacket soon. This one won’t do.

Text.SourceString: I try not to go to the forest. There are way too many wasps.
Text.LocalizedString: I try not to go to the forest. There are way too many wasps.

Text.SourceString: You can upgrade your bug net to catch bugs more easily.//<portrait=surprised>Oh, no that’s not what I meant.//<portrait=normal>What I meant was you can <Italic>buy</> better-quality bug nets.
Text.LocalizedString: You can upgrade your bug net to catch bugs more easily.//<portrait=surprised>Oh, no that’s not what I meant.//<portrait=normal>What I meant was you can <Italic>buy</> better-quality bug nets.

Text.SourceString: We sell bug nets at the Beach Shack.//Sometimes, we even have nets of different quality. The better your net is, the wider its catching radius is.
Text.LocalizedString: We sell bug nets at the Beach Shack.//Sometimes, we even have nets of different quality. The better your net is, the wider its catching radius is.

Text.SourceString: I can’t promise you anything, though.//What we sell at the shack depends on what we can get.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t promise you anything, though.//What we sell at the shack depends on what we can get.

Text.SourceString: I hope I’m not wearing too many brooches today.//<portrait=happy>I couldn’t pick one, so I wore all three.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope I’m not wearing too many brooches today.//<portrait=happy>I couldn’t pick one, so I wore all three.

Text.SourceString: Little wood satyr butterflies are everywhere – around the lake, by the school, and even behind our house!//That’s how I know it’s Spring.
Text.LocalizedString: Little wood satyr butterflies are everywhere – around the lake, by the school, and even behind our house!//That’s how I know it’s Spring.

Text.SourceString: That and the no-snow thing.
Text.LocalizedString: That and the no-snow thing.

Text.SourceString: I got <NpcName>Sunny</> that brown sweater he’s wearing at White Flamingo.//It cost a fortune, but I can’t deny the quality.//<portrait=happy>It’s been years, and it’s held up better than I thought it would.
Text.LocalizedString: I got <NpcName>Sunny</> that brown sweater he’s wearing at White Flamingo.//It cost a fortune, but I can’t deny the quality.//<portrait=happy>It’s been years, and it’s held up better than I thought it would.

Text.SourceString: I’m glad I bought it, but I’m not sure if I’d get another one. Ha ha!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m glad I bought it, but I’m not sure if I’d get another one. Ha ha!

Text.SourceString: I want to be supportive of <NpcName>Oliver’s</> dream to become a police detective, even though it makes me nervous.//I want him to know I’ll always love him, whatever he does.//<portrait=concerned>I just hope I’ll be here for it.
Text.LocalizedString: I want to be supportive of <NpcName>Oliver’s</> dream to become a police detective, even though it makes me nervous.//I want him to know I’ll always love him, whatever he does.//<portrait=concerned>I just hope I’ll be here for it.

Text.SourceString: Fireflies are the prettiest bugs I’ve ever seen. They’re my favorite.
Text.LocalizedString: Fireflies are the prettiest bugs I’ve ever seen. They’re my favorite.

Text.SourceString: Not many people believe in it, but I think there’s a whole civilization under the water.//<NpcName>Alice</> thinks so too.
Text.LocalizedString: Not many people believe in it, but I think there’s a whole civilization under the water.//<NpcName>Alice</> thinks so too.

Text.SourceString: We got to talking about folklore and Coral Island history.//Suffice it to say, she convinced me.
Text.LocalizedString: We got to talking about folklore and Coral Island history.//Suffice it to say, she convinced me.

Text.SourceString: I studied a bit about ocean critters, and there are around forty different species in our sea.
Text.LocalizedString: I studied a bit about ocean critters, and there are around forty different species in our sea.

Text.SourceString: The ocean is big. It’s even bigger than the land. Seventy percent of the Earth’s surface is ocean – something like that.
Text.LocalizedString: The ocean is big. It’s even bigger than the land. Seventy percent of the Earth’s surface is ocean – something like that.

Text.SourceString: And how much of the ocean hasn’t been explored? A lot. We don’t know what’s down there.//That’s what <NpcName>Alice</> said. She made a compelling point, <PlayerName>$Player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: And how much of the ocean hasn’t been explored? A lot. We don’t know what’s down there.//That’s what <NpcName>Alice</> said. She made a compelling point, <PlayerName>$Player</>.

Text.SourceString: We had some very tall coconut trees near the house, but we had to cut them down.//<portrait=annoyed>They cost us our roof! You know how windy it gets at the beach. When the coconuts are bearing fruit, it’s a dangerous time for us.
Text.LocalizedString: We had some very tall coconut trees near the house, but we had to cut them down.//<portrait=annoyed>They cost us our roof! You know how windy it gets at the beach. When the coconuts are bearing fruit, it’s a dangerous time for us.

Text.SourceString: 3 am, bam! Coconut hits our roof. Sounded like an explosion.
Text.LocalizedString: 3 am, bam! Coconut hits our roof. Sounded like an explosion.
